00:39:37.980 --> 00:39:40.320
And we've heard
other people do it.

00:39:40.320 --> 00:39:42.750
And it's really just
having that internal check.

00:39:42.750 --> 00:39:45.140
And I think that's where also
practices like meditation

00:39:45.140 --> 00:39:48.090
can help, because you can
become more aware of what's

00:39:48.090 --> 00:39:49.869
going on on the inside.

00:39:49.869 --> 00:39:51.910
And then you can also do
something very concrete,

00:39:51.910 --> 00:39:54.160
which is-- and it can
sound a little cheesy,

00:39:54.160 --> 00:39:56.070
but it actually works,
research shows--

00:39:56.070 --> 00:39:58.292
writing yourself a
letter in the face--

00:39:58.292 --> 00:40:00.000
let's say you've just
failed at something

00:40:00.000 --> 00:40:02.305
and you feel completely
down about yourself.

00:40:02.305 --> 00:40:03.930
Writing a letter as
if you were writing

00:40:03.930 --> 00:40:05.720
to a friend to
whom this happened

00:40:05.720 --> 00:40:07.351
can be very therapeutic.

00:40:07.351 --> 00:40:08.600
So those are some of the ways.

00:40:08.600 --> 00:40:11.010
The other thing is also to
have a self-compassion mantra

00:40:11.010 --> 00:40:13.380
or some kind of phrase that
you already know by heart

00:40:13.380 --> 00:40:15.650
so that you can bring
it up in that moment.

00:40:15.650 --> 00:40:17.420
It could be-- whatever it is.

00:40:17.420 --> 00:40:20.620
In fact, the woman who started
research on self-compassion,

00:40:20.620 --> 00:40:22.380
she had a child with autism.

00:40:22.380 --> 00:40:24.180
And it was a little boy.

00:40:24.180 --> 00:40:27.410
And they were on a plane, and
he was having a huge crisis.

00:40:27.410 --> 00:40:28.980
And the bathrooms were closed.

00:40:28.980 --> 00:40:30.840
She couldn't get
into the bathroom.

00:40:30.840 --> 00:40:32.624
She had to be there
with him, making

00:40:32.624 --> 00:40:33.790
this huge fuss on the plane.

00:40:33.790 --> 00:40:35.260
There was nothing she could do.

00:40:35.260 --> 00:40:38.835
And that in that moment,
she became very aware

00:40:38.835 --> 00:40:40.210
of the impact of
self-compassion.

00:40:40.210 --> 00:40:42.340
If she could soothe
herself in that moment,

00:40:42.340 --> 00:40:44.490
she could handle that
crisis, which there was

00:40:44.490 --> 00:40:46.110
nothing she could do otherwise.

00:40:46.110 --> 00:40:47.812
So it's very powerful.

00:40:47.812 --> 00:40:50.020
And she suggests having
these self-compassion matras,

00:40:50.020 --> 00:40:53.350
so maybe just a phrase
that you bring to mind

00:40:53.350 --> 00:40:55.500
and that you just know
ahead of time that you

00:40:55.500 --> 00:40:57.150
can tell yourself.

00:40:57.150 --> 00:40:57.770
Yeah.

